column5: Well after a couple of skunk trips this week I finally managed to catch a few saugeyes, Went for about an hour after work yesterday and caught two.   Hit it real good this morning, probably caught twenty of the little buggers.      All fish came on jig/wtwister on a current break in 15' of water. All small fish but what the hey I had a blast, not bad for December 30. Going to have to scout a few more spots to find the bigger ones or wait for some colder weather because they will come  Whopper
You done good Phil! Little'uns are better than none! Nice pics... yer really gettin' the hang of the self timer eh?
i should load the car and come down now , great catchin small uns are better than el skunko anytime
LOL Phil where is the snow?
WTG Phil, their  a heck of alot bigger than any fish I caught this weekend
Good going, as Lew said but only I haven't caught a fish since Nov...
Smaller is better than none, I haven't caught a fish since October...  Mike
Nice fish Phil. Fishing so far up this way has been a bit tough with all the warm weather so far. Nice to see some eyes being caught.
You lose weight Phil ??? Oh no...it's the fish that did! lol  Great stuff buddy! Glad to see you getting out there and wetting a line in late December!
....I'd be happy with an outing like Phil. Beats waiting for the lakes to freeze over.
Way to go Whopper.  Spiel i think you said it right.

Thanks everyone! Couldn't stand it had to go back again today   , ending the year with a three fish outing and what a year it has been!  I really hate for it to end.   I hope everyone here at OFC has a Happy New Year! The Mrs and I are going out to celebrate!  Best Fishes for 2007
Nice going Phil, thanks for the report. Hope you have more of them in the near future, ice regardless.

Phil,nice looking saugeyes bud,have not caught one of them since I left Montreal years ago, do you guys have a slot limit on them your way,cause they are the right size to eat. Now go catch the bigger ones Phil.  Steve
